<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="911" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d911">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.52/201: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-03T00:00:00-05:00">October 3,
                                    1941—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>538. Your 874, October 1, 8 p.m. It is suggested that the opening words
                            of paragraph 3 be modified to read as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Moreover my government has continued to supply Spain with
                                    petroleum products and other urgently needed products despite
                                    the fact that the Spanish Government has excluded” et
                                    cetera.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>